content: Morning Ruby, heads up, I've got a last-minute trip to Seoul starting Wed. Need travel plan v2.0 please.
Got it, Rohanüëç I'll coordinate with the team today. Will handle flights, gym pass, and local contacts. Anything urgent on your side before I lock the plan?
Nothing urgent, just make sure it works with my CGM setup.
Morning, I'll adapt your jet lag protocol for Seoul (+1 hr from Singapore). Will also sync meal/light exposure with CGM patterns.
I'll research a nearby gym with the right equipment for your current program. Will confirm by tonight.
Noted - will prep a Korea-friendly nutrition guide factoring local dishes + CGM. Will send before you fly.
This is a good chance to stress-test the plan in a new market. Will add a note to review data post-trip for insights.
Quick update - found a gym 5min walk from hotel, English-speaking staff. Temporary pass confirmed. Will include in your travel kit.
Jet lag plan ready: shift meals 30 mins earlier each day starting today, 20min morning sunlight in Seoul.
Noted. Will start today.
Also added local emergency contact (English-speaking doctor). Will send full PDF protocol tonight.
Sent your 'Travel Protocol v2.0' doc to your email. Let me know if anything's unclear.
Protocol looks solid. Thanks Ruby!
Safe flight later today! You're all set - gym pass, doctor contact, nutrition guide, and CGM supplies packed?
Yep, all packed. Appreciate the prep.
How's Seoul so far? (KST now)
Landed an hour ago. Hotel's fine. Will hit the gym in AM.
Carla - CGM spiked after lunch. Had bibimbap w/gochujang.
Likely from gochujang's sugar + rice. Next meal: start w/banchan veg, then protein, then carbs. Let's see if curve flattens.
Copy that. Will try at dinner.
Team dinner ran long, couldn't stick to plan fully.
No worries - just prioritize protein + fiber next time, and do a 10min walk now to help glucose drop.
Walking back to hotel now.
How's energy in the gym? And mental focus tracking on trip?
Gym's good, focus score dipped a bit yesterday but fine today.
Noted. Will cross-ref with CGM + sleep data when you're back.
Your return flight is still Sat 9pm KST, right? Just confirming for pickup logistics.
Yes, still on schedule.
Tried the breakfast swap test yet? Curious about CGM curve.
Sorry missed this yesterday - yes, swapped to eggs + avocado. Spike was way lower.
Perfect. That's the kind of data we can build into your core plan.
Landing arrangements in Singapore are sorted. Your driver will be waiting at T3.
Thanks Ruby. This was smooth.
Let's debrief Monday ‚Äî want to capture travel learnings + CGM insights while fresh.
Sounds good. Appreciate all the support this week üôè
Always a pleasure to keep things frictionless for you, Rohan üòä
